## 2.3 Critical Data Flows

### 2.3.1 Daily Operational Flow

```
06:00 │ CSV file drop (mileage.csv) → File Watcher detects
06:05 │ Ingestion Worker: Parse, validate, insert mileage readings
06:10 │ Ingestion Worker: Update train current_mileage, detect anomalies
06:15 │ Drift Monitor: Check against baseline, flag significant deviations
06:30 │ Optimizer Worker: Generate today's run assignments
      │   - Input: trains, routes, constraints, inventory positions
      │   - Output: assignments with explanation traces
07:00 │ WebSocket: Push results to connected canvas clients
07:00 │ Operators: Review assignments on Infinite Canvas
      │   - View explanation factors for each assignment
      │   - Drag-and-drop to override if needed (with audit trail)
08:00 │ Export: Approved assignments sent to OCC system
16:00 │ Actual mileage updates (if available intra-day)
22:00 │ Optimizer Worker: Generate tomorrow's assignments
```

### 2.3.2 Weekly Planning Flow

```
Monday 06:00  │ Strategic Planner: Run 10-year horizon update
              │   - Uses constraint envelope from tactical model
              │   - Respects published baseline (drift threshold)
Monday 06:30  │ Tactical Scheduler: Run 12-week PM scheduling
              │   - Check material availability for T+14 days (hard)
              │   - Check material availability for T+90 days (soft)
Monday 07:00  │ Man-hour Leveling: Generate 12-week projection
              │   - Identify overloaded/underutilized weeks
              │   - Propose adjustments (defer/advance/overtime)
Monday 08:00  │ WebSocket: Push updated canvas data to all clients
Tuesday       │ Planners: Review PM conflicts on canvas
              │   - Drag to resolve conflicts (audit trail)
              │   - Review/approve man-hour adjustments
Wednesday    │ Report Worker: Generate resource utilization report
Friday       │ Notification Worker: Send weekly compliance report
```

### 2.3.3 Baseline Publishing Flow

```
User Action  │ Planner clicks "Publish Baseline" on canvas
             │   - System validates: no critical conflicts
             │   - System prompts: "This will create Baseline v3.2"
API Call     │ POST /api/v1/baselines
             │   - Snapshot current pm_schedule to baseline_pm_schedule
             │   - Snapshot mileage projections to baseline_mileage_projection
             │   - Set previous baseline status to SUPERSEDED
             │   - Set new baseline status to PUBLISHED
Post-Publish │ Drift Monitor: Now compares against new baseline
             │ Canvas: Shows drift layer relative to new baseline
```

### 2.3.4 Scenario Comparison Flow

```
User Action  │ Planner clicks "Create Scenario" on canvas
             │   - System forks from current published baseline
             │   - New scenario_id assigned
Editing      │ Planner makes changes within scenario
             │   - All changes stored as deltas (event-sourced)
             │   - Original baseline data unchanged
Comparison   │ Planner clicks "Compare Scenarios"
             │   - System materializes both scenarios
             │   - Canvas shows side-by-side diff view
             │   - Metrics: cost impact, resource utilization delta
Promotion    │ Planner clicks "Promote to Baseline"
             │   - Deltas applied to create new baseline
             │   - Scenario marked as PROMOTED
```

